d jars. I need to evaluate things without running them, and the syntax looks like this:\\n\\nI might have a potential conflict due to the built-in scalaCompilerPlugins. Is it okay to name it \\\"scalaCompiler\\\"? With ScalaCompile, I need the correct classpath, and I’m curious if I need to import ScalaCompile. \\n\\nIt seems like the compiler version usually should match the library version, but maybe it can compile against an older one. I’ll have to consider the compatibility and warnings.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Scala binary compatibility**\\n\\nI think Scala version 2.13.8 should be okay for binary compatibility across patches. But what if the bytecode refers to methods in scala-library 2.13.16 that aren't available in 2.13.8? The compiler usually emits stable code. If the source uses `Either.partitionMap`, it might still compile with the 2.13.8 standard library. So, I’ll go ahead and implement this, then decide on amending the current commit or creating a new one. Should I reset? I’ll modify build.gradle too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pH21R8qNpP15ftjZvsnOQ6FY|fc_0b279b993ce707de0169fa3463569081918d5579cc02b05b68", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-compiler/2.13.8/build.gradle", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\nplugins {\n    id \"org.graalvm.internal.tck\"\n    id \"scala\"\n}\n\nString libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n\nconfigurations {\n    scalaCompilerToolchain\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    testImplementation \"org.scala-lang:scala-compiler:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n    testImplementation \"org.scala-lang:scala-library:$libraryVersion\"\n    scalaCompilerToolchain 'org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.13.16'\n    scalaCompilerToolchain 'org.scala-lang:scala-compiler:2.13.16'\n}\n\ntasks.withType(ScalaCompile).configureEach {\n    scalaClasspath = configurations.scalaCompilerToolchain\n}\n\njava {\n    toolchain {\n        languageVersion = JavaLanguageVersion.of(21)\n    }\n}\n\ngraalvmNative {\n    agent {\n        defaultMode = \"conditional\"\n        modes {\n            conditional {\n                userCodeFilterPath = \"user-code-filter.json\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 441, "output": 1487, "cacheRead": 75776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 77704, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778005073478, "responseId": "resp_0b279b993ce707de0169fa345232c481919abc42ea67a1b204"}}
