[assistant] Fixed the `compileTestScala` failure.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - Gradle was using `scala-compiler:2.13.8` to compile the test sources.
[assistant] - Scala compiler `2.13.8` cannot reliably parse newer JDK 21 class files, causing `bad constant pool index`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Kept the tested/runtime dependencies versioned by `libraryVersion`.
[assistant] - Added a separate Scala compiler toolchain configuration using `scala-compiler:2.13.16` only for compiling the test sources.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit:
[assistant] - `137743226 Fix scala-compiler test compilation`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the tests locally, per instruction.
[assistant-event] text_end
