[assistant] Fixed the `compiler-bridge` error.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - The previous `scalaClasspath` override removed Gradle/Zinc’s expected compiler bridge from the Scala compiler classpath.
[assistant] - Gradle’s Scala plugin expects the bridge to remain available, so overriding `scalaClasspath` directly was too broad.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Removed the custom `scalaCompilerToolchain` configuration and `scalaClasspath` override.
[assistant] - Restored the standard pattern used elsewhere in the repo:
[assistant]   - keep the tested compiler dependency via `libraryVersion`
[assistant]   - add `scala-library:2.13.16`
[assistant]   - add `scala-compiler:2.13.16`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated commit:
[assistant] - `f70c4a2a5 Fix scala-compiler test compilation`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the tests locally, per instruction.
